name: phosphoglycerate dehydrogenase
classes: Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
comment: This enzyme catalyses the first committed and rate-limiting step in the phosphoserine pathway of serine biosynthesis. The reaction occurs predominantly in the direction of reduction. The enzyme from the bacterium Escherichia coli also catalyses the activity of EC 1.1.1.399, 2-oxoglutarate reductase [6].
